1. Assign an initial value to the LinearWrite index for each word in the text, setting it to 1 for words with 2 or fewer syllables and 3 for words with more than three syllables.

2. For every proposition (i.e., complete sentence) in the text, calculate the total LinearWrite index by summing the indices of all words within that proposition.

3. Divide the calculated LinearWrite index by the number of propositions to get an average LinearWrite index per proposition.

4. If the average LinearWrite index is greater than 20, divide it by 2. Otherwise, subtract 1 from the result of dividing the average LinearWrite index by 2.

5. The final adjusted LinearWrite index results from this calculation.
